            <section>
               <id root="b7caba61-cf34-4a13-bc06-75a53533a505"/>
               <code code="51945-4" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="PACKAGE LABEL.PRINCIPAL DISPLAY PANEL"/>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>REFRIGERATED LIQUID<br/>NITROGEN, REFRIGERATED LIQUID UN1977<br/>NON-FLAMMABLE GAS  2     ALWAYS KEEP CONTAINER IN UPRIGHT POSITION    DO NOT CHANGE OR FORCE FIT CONNECTIONS<br/>Rx only. CAUTION: Federal law prohibits dispensing without prescription. WARNING: EXTREMELY COLD LIQUID AND GAS UNDERPRESSURE. CAN CAUSE RAPID SUFFOCATION. CAN CAUSE SEVERE FROSTBITE. Store and use with adequate ventilation. Do not get liquid in eyes, on skin or clothing. For liquid withdrawal, wear face shield and gloves. Do not drop. Use suitable hand truck for container movement. Cylinder temperature should not exceed 52C (125F). Close valve after each use and when empty. Use a back flow preventive device in the piping. Use in accordance with Material Safety Data Sheet (MSDS).<br/>IF INHALED, remove to fresh air. If not breathing, give artificial respiration. If breathing is difficult, give oxygen. Call a physician.  CAS: 7727-37-9<br/>DO NOT REMOVE THIS PRODUCT LABEL.<br/>AIRGAS PURITAN MEDICAL  Airgas West, Inc.  Lakewood, CA 90712 (562) 497-1991<br/>843549 (12/04)<renderMultiMedia referencedObject="MM2"/>
                  </paragraph>
               </text>
